		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Cupertino, CA 3-6-02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.86)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1093'>Steve "Buba_Fatz" Daniel</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=1093&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 7, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Ok, I started playing LotR about a month ago, and became a Product Champion (swtiched from SW).  Since then, I have amassed a decent collection, with 2 playsets of rares and playsets of the really good ones (mains, hate, double shot, etc.).  The only tournaments that have been available were league night, commons only (got 2nd), two sealed (got 4th in both)...until tonight!<br />
<br />
Tonight was a constructed tournament, and I had no deck.  I put together a Gimli/Legolas/Gandalf deck but it sucked, so with an hour to go I put together a fast Moria/Ranger deck (will be coming soon on my page).  It&#39;s basically make Aragorn, Arwen, and Legolas beefy, use archery to kill, and Gandalf to suck up damage (i.e. Balrog was legal today).  Moria was swarm, pretty standard, with a Balrog (not so important really, rather have 10 guys!).  I get there early, and when the dust settles there are 14 of us.  Onto it! <br />
<br />
Rating Before: 1500 (no tournament experience yet)<br />
Deck: Moria/Archer/Ranger madness<br />
<br />
GAME 1: Me vs. Chris Scott&#39;s 100 card pile.<br />
His deck was huge, and he only started Gimli so I was like &quot;easy win.&quot;  Chris isn&#39;t new, but he also isn&#39;t too experienced.  I go first, get Aragorn, move...move again.  He dropped like one guy who ate it to archery.  His turn, he just moves, I do nothing, he moves again I throw out a couple guys and an Armory...my turn, I move to site four, kill Enquea then stop.  I draw runner, armory, scimitar, troll&#39;s keyward, and cave troll.  Need 5 twilight to do it.  He moves to Mithril Mine...5 twilight...armory, runner (6), scimitar (8), keyward (5), troll.  Game.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
TOTAL = 3<br />
<br />
So we talk a little bit, cause we&#39;re the first ones done, and then we hear the next pairings get ready to go.  I get paired up with the best there, Chris Larkin (fellow PC) and am thinking &quot;great.&quot;<br />
<br />
GAME 2: Me vs. Chris Larkin&#39;s Ranger/Nazgul<br />
I know he uses Nazgul so I bid low, and let him go first since he starts Pony.  So no Nazgul sites..he goes to 3 with minimal resistance.  I go to 2, get hit with a Nazgul, stop.  I am dumping fellowship for shadow because I can&#39;t do as well vs. Nazgul.  He goes from 3 to 4, little guys come out, a couple on swarms. He stops.  I go to 3, he gets out nothing I stop.  He goes to 5...down comes a few guys, no troll yet, and I get a scavengers on swarms...he stops...my turn, I move to 4 meet a Nazgul, then stop...my hand is almost all minions with 2 moria scouts.  My turn, he moves, i drop scavengers, scimitar, moria scout x3 (drew one), a couple runners, keyward, wallcrawler, some more scimitars and troll.  All in all, 12 guys...3-4 bite it to archery, but the rest live and overwhelm Frodo.  Best swarm I&#39;ve ever done.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
TOTAL = 6<br />
<br />
I&#39;m realy psyched now, and ready to rumble.  Chris is a bit disgruntled because he is going to lose ratings :)<br />
<br />
GAME 3: Me vs. Alfred Dong&#39;s &quot;Don&#39;t Pee in the Twilight Pool&quot;<br />
Alfred doesn&#39;t have many cards, and I helped him get all the rares needed to play Alex Tennet&#39;s deck so I know what to expect.  I go first, grab Aragorn, move along.  He goes, gives me no twilight, I drop an armory and some stuff.  My turn, move to 4 stop.  He goes to 4, stops. I go to 5, face troll plus others but come out barely hurt...dropped Gandalf at site 4 in case he decided to bring out the Balrog (added him and ARV) but he drops 2 guys then balrog...Gandalf takes 2, Aragorn takes 2 and i stop.  He moves in, and the Troll + a couple guys take down Aragorn...now just Frodo :).  My go, I move, stop.  He moves and PATHS away my guys.  I go, move again and ARV to take out a couple guys, stop.  Next turn, I drop 3 or 4 guys and he concedes with a shadow hand.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
TOTAL = 9<br />
<br />
I find out that myslef and one other guy (steve, works at store) are undefeated and the winner takes the tournament, so the pressure is on.<br />
<br />
GAME 4: Me vs. Steve&#39;s borrowed Shoulder Fire deck<br />
This was a nazgul/moria dwarf/elf deck that used lot&#39;s of wound spreading and beefy guys to take me down.  I go first, move twice, stop.  He goes, wipes ou a runner, and then stops.  I go to 4, nothing happens, stop.  He goes, moves to 4, stops.  I drop Gandaleasterlingain anticipating balrog but he decides to drop Cantea, Attea, Witch King...ouch...Legolas and Gandalf die, and Aragorn/Arwen are exhausted...uh oh.  He moves to 4 with arwen/aragorn/legolas/frodo.  I pull out the Balrog, and at this point arwen is 8 strength, aragorn is 8, legolas is 6, and frodo is, well, frodo.  So he needs to choose who dies, since Arwen had a wound on her (forgot why).  He picks that arwen and legolas die, then stings my hand, sees Scavengers and Cave Troll, then moves one...9 in pool, drop Scavengers for 1 (dimrill dale), scimitar adds 2 (armory) and then troll.  Dead aragorn, and then next turn I move into sanctuary, and his turn I drop 4 guys for the win.<br />
<br />
FW +3<br />
TOTAL = 12<br />
<br />
Well, my first real tournament and I won it.  Hot gosh darnit!  Prizes were small, entrance was 1 pack each, and we opened the packs and first got to pick...best 3 were Gandalf, FotS...Lurtz + a common foil...or Morgul Gates + Blade of Gondor foil...took the Gates of course :)<br />
<br />
After, did some trading and stuff and got some cool cards.  Cards of the day for me were = Double Shot, Cave Troll, Armory, and just plain archery.  Gotta love archery.<br />
<br />
PROPS:<br />
Superstars for another awesome tournament<br />
My two free packs of MoM for giving me a Witch King<br />
Mike for the awesome trades<br />
Jeff for the odd trade<br />
My opponents for being stepping stones :) j/k<br />
<br />
SLOPS:<br />
Gary for that pack trade! j/k man, it&#39;s cool!<br />
<br />
Thanks for reading, and give me a 5!  My first TR!<br />
